That proves much easier said than done. The main alleyway was clearly designed to be used to some degree, but these little extra paths seem to be completely coincidental, springing up as buildings in this more dense part of town cropped up with no real rhyme or reason. As a result, they twist and turn in ways that defy reason. It should have been pretty easy to just sneak by those horndogs, just go down a bit, right, and then back up, no? It doesn’t help that so many of these pathways go forward a while, before randomly ending in a dead end, or just becoming so narrow that you can’t possibly squeeze through them. Or at least, not without covering yourself in alley grease, ugh. Somehow, in your aimless wandering, you come across a spot that opens up in a little alley alcove of sorts. Quite the interesting find, but you should really figure a way out of here.
